20 /**
21 * @addtogroup Interrupt_vector_numbers_GROUP Interrupt vector numbers
22 * @brief Vector numbers required for NVIC functions
23 * @{
24 */
25 /* ------------------------- Interrupt Number Definition ------------------------ */
26 
27 /**
28  * Interrupt vector numbers
29  */
30 typedef enum {
31 /* ------------------------ Processor Exceptions Numbers ------------------------- */
32  Reset_IRQn = -15, /**< 1 Reset Vector, invoked on Power up and warm reset */
33  NonMaskableInt_IRQn = -14, /**< 2 Non maskable Interrupt, cannot be stopped or preempted */
34  HardFault_IRQn = -13, /**< 3 Hard Fault, all classes of Fault */
35  MemoryManagement_IRQn = -12, /**< 4 Memory Management, MPU mismatch, including Access Violation and No Match */
36  BusFault_IRQn = -11, /**< 5 Bus Fault, Pre-Fetch-, Memory Access Fault, other address/memory related Fault */
37  UsageFault_IRQn = -10, /**< 6 Usage Fault, i.e. Undef Instruction, Illegal State Transition */
38  SVCall_IRQn = -5, /**< 11 System Service Call via SVC instruction */
39  DebugMonitor_IRQn = -4, /**< 12 Debug Monitor */
40  PendSV_IRQn = -2, /**< 14 Pendable request for system service */
41  SysTick_IRQn = -1, /**< 15 System Tick Timer */
42 /* ---------------------- MK20D5 VectorTable ---------------------- */
43  DMA0_IRQn = 0, /**< 16 Direct memory access controller */
44  DMA1_IRQn = 1, /**< 17 Direct memory access controller */
45  DMA2_IRQn = 2, /**< 18 Direct memory access controller */
46  DMA3_IRQn = 3, /**< 19 Direct memory access controller */
47  DMA_Error_IRQn = 4, /**< 20 DMA error interrupt */
48  FTF_Command_IRQn = 6, /**< 22 Flash Memory Interface */
49  FTF_ReadCollision_IRQn = 7, /**< 23 Flash Memory Interface */
50  PMC_IRQn = 8, /**< 24 Power Management Controller */
51  LLWU_IRQn = 9, /**< 25 Low Leakage Wakeup */
52  WDOG_IRQn = 10, /**< 26 External Watchdog Monitor */
53  I2C0_IRQn = 11, /**< 27 Inter-Integrated Circuit */
54  SPI0_IRQn = 12, /**< 28 Serial Peripheral Interface */
55  I2S0_Tx_IRQn = 13, /**< 29 Synchronous Serial Interface */
56  I2S0_Rx_IRQn = 14, /**< 30 Synchronous Serial Interface */
57  UART0_Lon_IRQn = 15, /**< 31 Serial Communication Interface */
58  UART0_RxTx_IRQn = 16, /**< 32 Serial Communication Interface */
59  UART0_Error_IRQn = 17, /**< 33 Serial Communication Interface */
60  UART1_RxTx_IRQn = 18, /**< 34 Serial Communication Interface */
61  UART1_Error_IRQn = 19, /**< 35 Serial Communication Interface */
62  UART2_RxTx_IRQn = 20, /**< 36 Serial Communication Interface */
63  UART2_Error_IRQn = 21, /**< 37 Serial Communication Interface */
64  ADC0_IRQn = 22, /**< 38 Analogue to Digital Converter */
65  CMP0_IRQn = 23, /**< 39 High-Speed Comparator */
66  CMP1_IRQn = 24, /**< 40 High-Speed Comparator */
67  FTM0_IRQn = 25, /**< 41 FlexTimer Module */
68  FTM1_IRQn = 26, /**< 42 FlexTimer Module */
69  CMT_IRQn = 27, /**< 43 Carrier Modulator Transmitter */
70  RTC_Alarm_IRQn = 28, /**< 44 Real Time Clock */
71  RTC_Seconds_IRQn = 29, /**< 45 Real Time Clock */
72  PIT0_IRQn = 30, /**< 46 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
73  PIT1_IRQn = 31, /**< 47 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
74  PIT2_IRQn = 32, /**< 48 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
75  PIT3_IRQn = 33, /**< 49 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
76  PDB0_IRQn = 34, /**< 50 Programmable Delay Block */
77  USB0_IRQn = 35, /**< 51 Universal Serial Bus */
78  USBDCD0_IRQn = 36, /**< 52 USB Device Charger Detection */
79  TSI0_IRQn = 37, /**< 53 Touch Sense Interface */
80  MCG_IRQn = 38, /**< 54 Multipurpose Clock Generator */
81  LPTMR0_IRQn = 39, /**< 55 Low Power Timer */
82  PORTA_IRQn = 40, /**< 56 General Purpose Input/Output */
83  PORTB_IRQn = 41, /**< 57 General Purpose Input/Output */
84  PORTC_IRQn = 42, /**< 58 General Purpose Input/Output */
85  PORTD_IRQn = 43, /**< 59 General Purpose Input/Output */
86  PORTE_IRQn = 44, /**< 60 General Purpose Input/Output */
87  SWI_IRQn = 45, /**< 61 Software interrupt */
88 } IRQn_Type;

169 #define __Vendor_SysTickConfig 0 /**< Whether Vendor implemented SYSTICK timer is present */

226 /* ================================================================================ */
227 
228 /**
229  * @brief Analog-to-Digital Converter
230  */
231 #define ADC_SC1_COUNT 2 /**< Number of ADC channels */
232 /**
233 * @addtogroup ADC_structs_GROUP ADC struct
234 * @brief Struct for ADC
235 * @{
236 */
237 typedef struct ADC_Type {
238  __IO uint32_t SC1[ADC_SC1_COUNT]; /**< 0000: Status and Control Register 1 */
239  __IO uint32_t CFG1; /**< 0008: Configuration Register 1 */
240  __IO uint32_t CFG2; /**< 000C: Configuration Register 2 */
241  __I uint32_t R[ADC_SC1_COUNT]; /**< 0010: Data Result Register */
242  __IO uint32_t CV1; /**< 0018: Compare Value */
243  __IO uint32_t CV2; /**< 001C: Compare Value */
244  __IO uint32_t SC2; /**< 0020: Status and Control Register 2 */
245  __IO uint32_t SC3; /**< 0024: Status and Control Register 3 */
246  __IO uint32_t OFS; /**< 0028: Offset Correction Register */
247  __IO uint32_t PG; /**< 002C: Plus-Side Gain Register */
248  __IO uint32_t MG; /**< 0030: Minus-Side Gain Register */
249  __IO uint32_t CLPD; /**< 0034: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
250  __IO uint32_t CLPS; /**< 0038: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
251  __IO uint32_t CLP4; /**< 003C: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
252  __IO uint32_t CLP3; /**< 0040: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
253  __IO uint32_t CLP2; /**< 0044: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
254  __IO uint32_t CLP1; /**< 0048: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
255  __IO uint32_t CLP0; /**< 004C: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
256  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4]; /**< 0050: 0x4 bytes */
257  __IO uint32_t CLMD; /**< 0054: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
258  __IO uint32_t CLMS; /**< 0058: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
259  __IO uint32_t CLM4; /**< 005C: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
260  __IO uint32_t CLM3; /**< 0060: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
261  __IO uint32_t CLM2; /**< 0064: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
262  __IO uint32_t CLM1; /**< 0068: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
263  __IO uint32_t CLM0; /**< 006C: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
264 } ADC_Type;
265

1045 */

1056  };

1062  };
1063  };
1064  };
1065  };

1071  };
1072  };

1078  };
1079  };

1234  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI1; /**< 0102: Channel 1 Priority Register */
1235  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI0; /**< 0103: Channel 0 Priority Register */
1236  };

1238  };
1239  uint8_t RESERVED_6[3836]; /**< 0104: 0xEFC bytes */
1240  struct {

1261  };
1262  } TCD[4]; /**< 1000: (cluster: size=0x0080, 128) */

3160  * @brief FlexTimer Module (2 channels)
3161  */
3162 #define FTM1_CONTROLS_COUNT 2 /**< Number of FTM channels */
3163 /**
3164 * @addtogroup FTM_structs_GROUP FTM struct
3165 * @brief Struct for FTM
3166 * @{
3167 */
3168 typedef struct FTM1_Type {
3169  __IO uint32_t SC; /**< 0000: Status and Control */
3170  __IO uint32_t CNT; /**< 0004: Counter */
3171  __IO uint32_t MOD; /**< 0008: Modulo */
3172  struct {
3173  __IO uint32_t CnSC; /**< 000C: Channel Status and Control */
3174  __IO uint32_t CnV; /**< 0010: Channel Value */
3175  } CONTROLS[FTM1_CONTROLS_COUNT]; /**< 000C: (cluster: size=0x0010, 16) */
3176  uint8_t RESERVED_1[48]; /**< 001C: 0x30 bytes */
3177  __IO uint32_t CNTIN; /**< 004C: Counter Initial Value */
3178  __IO uint32_t STATUS; /**< 0050: Capture and Compare Status */
3179  __IO uint32_t MODE; /**< 0054: Features Mode Selection */
3180  __IO uint32_t SYNC; /**< 0058: Synchronization */
3181  __IO uint32_t OUTINIT; /**< 005C: Initial State for Channels Output */
3182  __IO uint32_t OUTMASK; /**< 0060: Output Mask */
3183  __IO uint32_t COMBINE; /**< 0064: Function for Linked Channels */
3184  __IO uint32_t DEADTIME; /**< 0068: Deadtime Insertion Control */
3185  __IO uint32_t EXTTRIG; /**< 006C: FTM External Trigger */
3186  __IO uint32_t POL; /**< 0070: Channels Polarity */
3187  __IO uint32_t FMS; /**< 0074: Fault Mode Status */
3188  __IO uint32_t FILTER; /**< 0078: Input Capture Filter Control */
3189  __IO uint32_t FLTCTRL; /**< 007C: Fault Control */
3190  __IO uint32_t QDCTRL; /**< 0080: Quadrature Decoder Control and Status */
3191  __IO uint32_t CONF; /**< 0084: Configuration */
3192  __IO uint32_t FLTPOL; /**< 0088: FTM Fault Input Polarity */
3193  __IO uint32_t SYNCONF; /**< 008C: Synchronization Configuration */
3194  __IO uint32_t INVCTRL; /**< 0090: FTM Inverting Control */
3195  __IO uint32_t SWOCTRL; /**< 0094: FTM Software Output Control */
3196  __IO uint32_t PWMLOAD; /**< 0098: FTM PWM Load */
3197 } FTM1_Type;

4771 #define PDB_DAC_COUNT 0 /**< Number of DAC outputs */

4773 #define PDB_POnDLY_COUNT 2 /**< Number of Pulse outputs */

4797  };

4799  };

6141 /**
6142  * @brief Serial Peripheral Interface
6143  */
6144 /**
6145 * @addtogroup SPI_structs_GROUP SPI struct
6146 * @brief Struct for SPI
6147 * @{
6148 */
6149 typedef struct SPI_Type {
6150  __IO uint32_t MCR; /**< 0000: Module Configuration Register */
6151  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4]; /**< 0004: 0x4 bytes */
6152  __IO uint32_t TCR; /**< 0008: Transfer Count Register */
6153  union { /**< 000C: (size=0008) */
6154  __IO uint32_t CTAR[2]; /**< 000C: Clock and Transfer Attributes Register (In Master Mode) */
6155  __IO uint32_t CTAR_SLAVE; /**< 000C: Clock and Transfer Attributes Register (In Slave Mode) */
6156  };
6157  uint8_t RESERVED_1[24]; /**< 0014: 0x18 bytes */
6158  __IO uint32_t SR; /**< 002C: Status register */
6159  __IO uint32_t RSER; /**< 0030: DMA/Interrupt Request Select and Enable Register */
6160  union { /**< 0034: (size=0004) */
6161  __IO uint32_t PUSHR; /**< 0034: PUSH TX FIFO Register In Master Mode */
6162  __IO uint32_t PUSHR_SLAVE; /**< 0034: PUSH TX FIFO Register In Slave Mode */
6163  };
6164  __I uint32_t POPR; /**< 0038: POP RX FIFO Register */
6165  __I uint32_t TXFR[4]; /**< 003C: Transmit FIFO */
6166  uint8_t RESERVED_2[48]; /**< 004C: 0x30 bytes */
6167  __I uint32_t RXFR[4]; /**< 007C: Receive FIFO */
6168 } SPI_Type;

6510  __I uint32_t FIFODATA0; /**< 0EEC: FIFODATA0 Register */
6511  __I uint32_t ITATBCTR2; /**< 0EF0: Integration Test ATB Control 2 Register */
6512  uint8_t RESERVED_4[4]; /**< 0EF4: 0x4 bytes */
6513  __I uint32_t ITATBCTR0; /**< 0EF8: Integration Test ATB Control 0 Register */
6514  __I uint32_t FIFODATA1; /**< 0EFC: FIFODATA1 Register */

6521  uint8_t RESERVED_7[4]; /**< 0FCC: 0x4 bytes */
6522  __I uint32_t PID4; /**< 0FD0: Peripheral Identification Register 4 */
6523  __I uint32_t PID5; /**< 0FD4: Peripheral Identification Register 5 */
6524  __I uint32_t PID6; /**< 0FD8: Peripheral Identification Register 6 */
6525  __I uint32_t PID7; /**< 0FDC: Peripheral Identification Register 7 */
6526  __I uint32_t PID0; /**< 0FE0: Peripheral Identification Register 0 */
6527  __I uint32_t PID1; /**< 0FE4: Peripheral Identification Register 1 */
6528  __I uint32_t PID2; /**< 0FE8: Peripheral Identification Register 2 */

6751 /**
6752  * @brief Touch Sensing Input
6753  */
6754 /**
6755 * @addtogroup TSI_structs_GROUP TSI struct
6756 * @brief Struct for TSI
6757 * @{
6758 */
6759 typedef struct TSI_Type {
6760  __IO uint32_t GENCS; /**< 0000: General Control and Status Register */
6761  __IO uint32_t SCANC; /**< 0004: SCAN Control Register */
6762  __IO uint32_t PEN; /**< 0008: Pin Enable Register */
6763  __I uint32_t WUCNTR; /**< 000C: Wake-Up Channel Counter Register */
6764  uint8_t RESERVED_0[240]; /**< 0010: 0xF0 bytes */
6765  union { /**< 0100: (size=0020) */
6766  struct { /**< 0100: (size=0020) */
6767  __I uint32_t CNTR1; /**< 0100: Counter Register 1 */
6768  __I uint32_t CNTR3; /**< 0104: Counter Register 3 */
6769  __I uint32_t CNTR5; /**< 0108: Counter Register 5 */
6770  __I uint32_t CNTR7; /**< 010C: Counter Register 7 */
6771  __I uint32_t CNTR9; /**< 0110: Counter Register 9 */
6772  __I uint32_t CNTR11; /**< 0114: Counter Register 11 */
6773  __I uint32_t CNTR13; /**< 0118: Counter Register 13 */
6774  __I uint32_t CNTR15; /**< 011C: Counter Register 15 */
6775  };
6776  __I uint16_t CNTR[16]; /**< 0100: Counter Register */
6777  };
6778  __IO uint32_t THRESHOLD; /**< 0120: Low Power Channel Threshold Register */
6779 } TSI_Type;

6977  __IO uint8_t MA2; /**< 0009: Match Address Registers 2 */

6982  __IO uint8_t IR; /**< 000E: Infrared Register */
6983  uint8_t RESERVED_0; /**< 000F: 0x1 bytes */
6984  __IO uint8_t PFIFO; /**< 0010: FIFO Parameters */
6985  __IO uint8_t CFIFO; /**< 0011: FIFO Control Register */
6986  __IO uint8_t SFIFO; /**< 0012: FIFO Status Register */

6989  __IO uint8_t RWFIFO; /**< 0015: FIFO Receive Watermark */
6990  __I uint8_t RCFIFO; /**< 0016: FIFO Receive Count */
6991  uint8_t RESERVED_1; /**< 0017: 0x1 bytes */
6992  __IO uint8_t C7816; /**< 0018: 7816 Control Register */
6993  __IO uint8_t IE7816; /**< 0019: 7816 Interrupt Enable Register */
6994  __IO uint8_t IS7816; /**< 001A: 7816 Interrupt Status Register */
6995  union { /**< 001B: (size=0001) */
6996  __IO uint8_t WP7816T0; /**< 001B: 7816 Wait Parameter Register */
6997  __IO uint8_t WP7816T1; /**< 001B: 7816 Wait Parameter Register */
6998  };
6999  __IO uint8_t WN7816; /**< 001C: 7816 Wait N Register */
7000  __IO uint8_t WF7816; /**< 001D: 7816 Wait FD Register */
7001  __IO uint8_t ET7816; /**< 001E: 7816 Error Threshold Register */
7002  __IO uint8_t TL7816; /**< 001F: 7816 Transmit Length Register */
7003  uint8_t RESERVED_2; /**< 0020: 0x1 bytes */
7004  __IO uint8_t C6; /**< 0021: CEA709.1-B Control Register 6 */
7005  __IO uint8_t PCTH; /**< 0022: CEA709.1-B Packet Cycle Time Counter High */
7006  __IO uint8_t PCTL; /**< 0023: CEA709.1-B Packet Cycle Time Counter Low */
7007  __IO uint8_t B1T; /**< 0024: CEA709.1-B Beta1 Timer */
7008  __IO uint8_t SDTH; /**< 0025: CEA709.1-B Secondary Delay Timer High */
7009  __IO uint8_t SDTL; /**< 0026: CEA709.1-B Secondary Delay Timer Low */
7010  __IO uint8_t PRE; /**< 0027: CEA709.1-B Preamble */
7011  __IO uint8_t TPL; /**< 0028: CEA709.1-B Transmit Packet Length */
7012  __IO uint8_t IE; /**< 0029: CEA709.1-B Interrupt Enable Register */
7013  __IO uint8_t WB; /**< 002A: CEA709.1-B WBASE */
7014  __IO uint8_t S3; /**< 002B: CEA709.1-B Status Register */
7015  __IO uint8_t S4; /**< 002C: CEA709.1-B Status Register */
7016  __I uint8_t RPL; /**< 002D: CEA709.1-B Received Packet Length */
7017  __I uint8_t RPREL; /**< 002E: CEA709.1-B Received Preamble Length */
7018  __IO uint8_t CPW; /**< 002F: CEA709.1-B Collision Pulse Width */
7019  __IO uint8_t RIDT; /**< 0030: CEA709.1-B Receive Indeterminate Time */
7020  __IO uint8_t TIDT; /**< 0031: CEA709.1-B Transmit Indeterminate Time */

7530  * @brief Universal Asynchronous Receiver/Transmitter
7531  */
7532 /**
7533 * @addtogroup UART_structs_GROUP UART struct
7534 * @brief Struct for UART
7535 * @{
7536 */
7537 typedef struct UART1_Type {
7538  __IO uint8_t BDH; /**< 0000: Baud Rate Register: High */
7539  __IO uint8_t BDL; /**< 0001: Baud Rate Register: Low */
7540  __IO uint8_t C1; /**< 0002: Control Register 1 */
7541  __IO uint8_t C2; /**< 0003: Control Register 2 */
7542  __I uint8_t S1; /**< 0004: Status Register 1 */
7543  __IO uint8_t S2; /**< 0005: Status Register 2 */
7544  __IO uint8_t C3; /**< 0006: Control Register 3 */
7545  __IO uint8_t D; /**< 0007: Data Register */
7546  __IO uint8_t MA1; /**< 0008: Match Address Registers 1 */
7547  __IO uint8_t MA2; /**< 0009: Match Address Registers 2 */
7548  __IO uint8_t C4; /**< 000A: Control Register 4 */
7549  __IO uint8_t C5; /**< 000B: Control Register 5 */
7550  __I uint8_t ED; /**< 000C: Extended Data Register */
7551  __IO uint8_t MODEM; /**< 000D: Modem Register */
7552  __IO uint8_t IR; /**< 000E: Infrared Register */
7553  uint8_t RESERVED_0; /**< 000F: 0x1 bytes */
7554  __IO uint8_t PFIFO; /**< 0010: FIFO Parameters */
7555  __IO uint8_t CFIFO; /**< 0011: FIFO Control Register */
7556  __IO uint8_t SFIFO; /**< 0012: FIFO Status Register */
7557  __IO uint8_t TWFIFO; /**< 0013: FIFO Transmit Watermark */
7558  __I uint8_t TCFIFO; /**< 0014: FIFO Transmit Count */
7559  __IO uint8_t RWFIFO; /**< 0015: FIFO Receive Watermark */
7560  __I uint8_t RCFIFO; /**< 0016: FIFO Receive Count */
7561 } UART1_Type;

7643 /**
7644  * @brief USB OTG Controller
7645  */
7646 /**
7647 * @addtogroup USB_structs_GROUP USB struct
7648 * @brief Struct for USB
7649 * @{
7650 */
7651 typedef struct USB_Type {
7652  __I uint8_t PERID; /**< 0000: Peripheral ID Register */
7653  uint8_t RESERVED_0[3]; /**< 0001: 0x3 bytes */
7654  __I uint8_t IDCOMP; /**< 0004: Peripheral ID Complement Register */
7655  uint8_t RESERVED_1[3]; /**< 0005: 0x3 bytes */
7656  __I uint8_t REV; /**< 0008: Peripheral Revision Register */
7657  uint8_t RESERVED_2[3]; /**< 0009: 0x3 bytes */
7658  __I uint8_t ADDINFO; /**< 000C: Peripheral Additional Info Register */
7659  uint8_t RESERVED_3[3]; /**< 000D: 0x3 bytes */
7660  __IO uint8_t OTGISTAT; /**< 0010: OTG Interrupt Status Register */
7661  uint8_t RESERVED_4[3]; /**< 0011: 0x3 bytes */
7662  __IO uint8_t OTGICR; /**< 0014: OTG Interrupt Control Register */
7663  uint8_t RESERVED_5[3]; /**< 0015: 0x3 bytes */
7664  __IO uint8_t OTGSTAT; /**< 0018: OTG Status Register */
7665  uint8_t RESERVED_6[3]; /**< 0019: 0x3 bytes */
7666  __IO uint8_t OTGCTL; /**< 001C: OTG Control Register */
7667  uint8_t RESERVED_7[99]; /**< 001D: 0x63 bytes */
7668  __IO uint8_t ISTAT; /**< 0080: Interrupt Status Register */
7669  uint8_t RESERVED_8[3]; /**< 0081: 0x3 bytes */
7670  __IO uint8_t INTEN; /**< 0084: Interrupt Enable Register */
7671  uint8_t RESERVED_9[3]; /**< 0085: 0x3 bytes */
7672  __IO uint8_t ERRSTAT; /**< 0088: Error Interrupt Status Register */
7673  uint8_t RESERVED_10[3]; /**< 0089: 0x3 bytes */
7674  __IO uint8_t ERREN; /**< 008C: Error Interrupt Enable Register */
7675  uint8_t RESERVED_11[3]; /**< 008D: 0x3 bytes */
7676  __I uint8_t STAT; /**< 0090: Status Register */
7677  uint8_t RESERVED_12[3]; /**< 0091: 0x3 bytes */
7678  __IO uint8_t CTL; /**< 0094: Control Register */
7679  uint8_t RESERVED_13[3]; /**< 0095: 0x3 bytes */
7680  __IO uint8_t ADDR; /**< 0098: Address Register */
7681  uint8_t RESERVED_14[3]; /**< 0099: 0x3 bytes */
7682  __IO uint8_t BDTPAGE1; /**< 009C: BDT Page Register 1 */
7683  uint8_t RESERVED_15[3]; /**< 009D: 0x3 bytes */
7684  __IO uint8_t FRMNUML; /**< 00A0: Frame Number Register Low */
7685  uint8_t RESERVED_16[3]; /**< 00A1: 0x3 bytes */
7686  __IO uint8_t FRMNUMH; /**< 00A4: Frame Number Register High */
7687  uint8_t RESERVED_17[3]; /**< 00A5: 0x3 bytes */
7688  __IO uint8_t TOKEN; /**< 00A8: Token Register */
7689  uint8_t RESERVED_18[3]; /**< 00A9: 0x3 bytes */
7690  __IO uint8_t SOFTHLD; /**< 00AC: SOF Threshold Register */
7691  uint8_t RESERVED_19[3]; /**< 00AD: 0x3 bytes */
7692  __IO uint8_t BDTPAGE2; /**< 00B0: BDT Page Register 2 */
7693  uint8_t RESERVED_20[3]; /**< 00B1: 0x3 bytes */
7694  __IO uint8_t BDTPAGE3; /**< 00B4: BDT Page Register 3 */
7695  uint8_t RESERVED_21[11]; /**< 00B5: 0xB bytes */
7696  struct {
7697  __IO uint8_t ENDPT; /**< 00C0: Endpoint Control Register */
7698  uint8_t RESERVED_22[3]; /**< 00C1: 0x3 bytes */
7699  } ENDPOINT[16]; /**< 00C0: (cluster: size=0x0040, 64) */
7700  __IO uint8_t USBCTRL; /**< 0100: USB Control Register */
7701  uint8_t RESERVED_23[3]; /**< 0101: 0x3 bytes */
7702  __I uint8_t OBSERVE; /**< 0104: USB OTG Observe Register */
7703  uint8_t RESERVED_24[3]; /**< 0105: 0x3 bytes */
7704  __IO uint8_t CONTROL; /**< 0108: USB OTG Control Register */
7705  uint8_t RESERVED_25[3]; /**< 0109: 0x3 bytes */
7706  __IO uint8_t USBTRC0; /**< 010C: USB Transceiver Control Register 0 */
7707  uint8_t RESERVED_26[7]; /**< 010D: 0x7 bytes */
7708  __IO uint8_t USBFRMADJUST; /**< 0114: Frame Adjust Register */
7709 } USB_Type;
7710 
7711 /**
7712  * @} */ /* End group USB_structs_GROUP
7713  */
